A man was killed in a Brooklyn shooting overnight, police said. The victim was shot multiple times at around 5:40 a.m. Saturday inside the Louis Armstrong Houses on the 300 block of Lexington Avenue in Bedford-Stuyvesant, cops said. The man, 46, was pronounced dead at Woodhull Hospital, authorities said. There are no arrests, and the investigation remains ongoing. Police are also searching for the suspect who gunned down a 33-year-old man in the Bronx Friday afternoon. The victim, Trevor Roberts, of Brooklyn, was shot in the chest at around 3 p.m. on East 174th Street, near Rosedale Avenue, cops said. EMS took Roberts to Jacobi Medical Center, where he was pronounced dead. There are no arrests.